39 NONPROFIT OWNERSHIP REQUIREMENTS FOR PROPERTY TAX EXEMPTION
40 SECTION 3.(a) G.S. 105-278.6 reads as rewritten:
41 "§ 105-278.6. Real and personal property used for charitable purposes.purposes by certain
42 entities.
43 (a) Real and personal property owned by:by an entity listed in this subsection is exempt
44 from taxation if (i) as to real property, it is actually and exclusively occupied and used, and as to
45 personal property, it is entirely and completely used, by the owner for a charitable purpose; and
46 (ii) the owner is not organized or operated for profit. The entities are:
47 (1) A Young Men's Christian Association or similar organization;organization.
48 (2) A home for the aged, sick, or infirm;infirm.
49 (3) An orphanage or similar home;home.
50 (4) A Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals;Animals.
51 (5) A reformatory or correctional institution;institution.
