10 (g) Compliance. – An eligible owner that has been granted an exemption under this
11 section must, on an annual basis by January 31 following the initial exemption, certify that it
12 remains in compliance with this section and provide to the taxing unit the items listed in
13 subdivision (3) of subsection (f) of this section, as of the previous December 31, including any
14 supporting documentation required by the taxing unit. Failure to meet these requirements within
15 the time limits subjects the property to discovery under G.S. 105-312. For purposes of satisfying
16 this requirement, the household income provided for each qualifying unit must be verified every
17 two years following initial verification of the tenant's income.
18 (h) Future Site. – Real property held by an eligible owner as a future site for affordable
19 rental housing may be classified under this section for no more than five years. The taxes that
20 would otherwise be due on real property exempt under this subsection are a lien on the property
21 as provided in G.S. 105-355(a). The taxes shall be carried forward in the records of the taxing
22 unit as deferred taxes. The deferred taxes are due and payable in accordance with
23 G.S. 105-277.1F when the property loses its eligibility for deferral as a result of a disqualifying
24 event. A disqualifying event occurs when the property is not used for affordable rental housing
25 that is in compliance with this section within five years from the first day of the fiscal year the
26 property was classified under this section. In addition to the provisions in G.S. 105-277.1F, all
27 liens arising under this subsection are extinguished when the property is used for affordable rental
28 housing within the time period allowed under this subsection. For purposes of this subsection,
29 the term "future site" means unimproved real property or improved real property that is not
30 occupied as of the date of the application for exemption under this section.
31 (i) Ineligible Property. – Property that has been designated a special class of property
32 under G.S. 105-277.16 and assessed accordingly is not eligible for exemption under this section."
