1 SECTION 3.(d) This section is effective for taxes imposed for taxable years
2 beginning on or after July 1, 2026, and, with respect to property held as a future site under
3 G.S. 105-278.6(e) or G.S. 105-278.7A(h), as enacted by this act, applies to real property
4 classified under those provisions on or after that date. Notwithstanding G.S. 105-282.1(a)(2)a.,
5 an owner of low- or moderate-income rental housing property that is exempt under
6 G.S. 105-278.6(a)(8) as of the effective date of this act must, by December 31, 2026, reapply for
7 the exemption, providing the assessor of the taxing unit with any necessary documentation for
8 compliance consistent with this act. Reapplication under this section is considered an application
9 under subsection (f) of G.S. 105-278.7A, as enacted by this act. Failure to meet this requirement
10 within the time limit subjects the property to discovery under G.S. 105-312.
